Game%20of%20Thrones%26quot%3B%20venture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Netflix%20series%20is%20based%20on%20Liu%20Cixin's%20%26quot%3BRemembrance%20of%20Earth's%20Past%26quot%3B%20trilogy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAlong%20with%20co-showrunner%20Alexander%20Woo%2C%20the%20pair%20craft%20a%20series%20that%20feels%20like%20a%20setup%20for%20something%20larger.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20go%20back%20and%20look%20at%20the%20first%20batch%20of%20reviews%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgame-of-thrones-prequel-spinoff-plans-timeline-hbo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHBO's%20%26quot%3BGame%20of%20Thrones%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20first%20blockbuster%20universe%20that%20David%20Benioff%20and%20D.B.%20Weiss%20succeeded%20in%20launching%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0you'd%20be%20forgiven%20for%20not%20believing%20you%20were%20reading%20about%20the%20zeitgeist-defining%20juggernaut%20it%20became.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20%26quot%3BGame%20of%20Thrones%26quot%3B%20bore%20the%20weight%20of%20living%20up%20to%20the%20prestige%20precedent%20set%20by%20medium-defining%20titles%20like%20%26quot%3BThe%20Sopranos%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20doing%20so%20while%20also%20being%20%26quot%3Bquasi-medieval%2C%20dragon-ridden%20fantasy%20crap%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fslate.com%2Fculture%2F2011%2F04%2Fgame-of-thrones-reviewed-prepare-thyself-for-quasi-medieval-dragon-ridden-fantasy-crap.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESlate%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20it%20at%20the%20time.%20It%20became%20the%20series%20that%20would%20define%20the%20network%20in%20the%202010s%2C%20setting%20a%20new%20standard%20for%20appointment%20viewing%20in%20the%20social%20media%20age.%20While%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fslate.com%2Fculture%2F2019%2F04%2Fgame-of-thrones-first-season-reviews-critics.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20reviewers%3C%2Fa%3E%20remarked%20on%20the%20show's%20great%20potential%2C%20others%20certainly%20weren't%20leaping%20to%20label%20it%20a%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20tell%20how%20%26quot%3B3%20Body%20Problem%26quot%3B%20will%20pan%20out%20even%20from%20its%20first%20season%2C%20which%20by%20the%20end%20still%20feels%20like%20it's%20only%20barely%20gotten%20started.%20Netflix%20certainly%20seems%20to%20hope%20that%20Benioff%20and%20Weiss%2C%20along%20with%20co-showrunner%20Alexander%20Woo%20(an%20HBO%20alum%20by%20way%20of%20%26quot%3BTrue%20Blood%26quot%3B)%2C%20can%20pull%20it%20off%20again%20and%20deliver%20yet%20another%20major%20genre%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%26quot%3B3%20Body%20Problem%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20oscillates%20from%20murder%20mystery%20to%20extraterrestrial%20sensibilities%20that%20should%20tickle%20any%20Carl%20Sagan%20fan's%20interest%2C%20sometimes%20feels%20too%20big%20for%20itself.%20Conversely%2C%20that%20large%20scope%20is%20also%20what%20makes%20it%20so%20compelling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EZine%20Tseng's%20performance%20as%20Wenjie%20is%20a%20standout%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222043%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20struggle%20session%20during%20the%20chinese%20cultural%20revolution%20in%20three%20body%20problem%2C%20with%20text%20in%20mandarin%20heralding%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20new%20age.%20hundreds%20hold%20up%20little%20red%20books%20as%20two%20red%20guards%20force%20a%20man%20down%20on%20stage%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eb6e0890413ab8e1db0198%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221532%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20struggle%20session%20depicted%20in%20%26quot%3B3%20Body%20Problem.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ENetflix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B3%20Body%20Problem%26quot%3B%20is%20based%20on%20Chinese%20author%20Liu%20Cixin's%20%26quot%3BRemembrance%20of%20Earth's%20Past%26quot%3B%20trilogy.%20The%20first%20novel%20of%20the%20series%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Three-Body%20Problem%2C%26quot%3B%20won%20the%202015%20Hugo%20Award.%20Before%20Netflix%20got%20its%20hands%20on%20it%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanityfair.com%2Fhollywood%2F2018%2F03%2Famazon-billion-the-three-body-problem%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereports%20circulated%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202018%20that%20Amazon's%20Prime%20Video%20was%20looking%20to%20adapt%20the%20story%20for%20a%20cool%20%241%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20series%20begins%20in%201966%20during%20the%20bloody%20Cultural%20Revolution%20in%20China.%20Young%20astrophysicist%20Ye%20Wenjie%20witnesses%20her%20father%20Ye%20Zhetai%2C%20a%20physics%20professor%20at%20Tsinghua%20University%2C%20beaten%20to%20death%20onstage%20during%20a%20struggle%20session%20where%20he's%20accused%20of%20being%20a%20counter-revolutionary.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20while%20working%20as%20part%20of%20a%20construction%20corps%20in%20Mongolia%2C%20she's%20caught%20with%20a%20taboo%20book%20and%20conscripted%20to%20put%20her%20science%20acumen%20to%20use%20at%20a%20military%20research%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%2C%20Wenjie%20sends%20a%20message%20into%20space.%20Miraculously%2C%20she%20gets%20a%20response%3A%20Do%20not%20respond%20to%20this%20message.%20If%20you%20do%2C%20my%20people%20will%20conquer%20your%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWenjie%20tells%20them%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20early%20sequences%20featuring%20Zine%20Tseng's%20sublime%20Wenjie%20(Rosalind%20Chao%20takes%20on%20the%20role%20later%20in%20the%20series%2C%20after%2040%20years%20have%20passed)%20are%20the%20bedrock%20of%20the%20series%2C%20thriving%20in%20the%20specificity%20of%20history.%20They%20manage%20to%20answer%20an%20impossible%20question%20crucial%20to%20the%20show's%20ethos%3A%20How%20does%20a%20human%20come%20to%20willingly%2C%20actively%20believe%20their%20species%20is%20so%20far%20beyond%20saving%20that%20they%20invite%20conquest%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20brilliant%20debut%20performance%2C%20Tseng%20manages%20to%20tread%20the%20fine%20line%20between%20sympathy%20and%20steel%2C%20and%20director%20Derek%20Tsang%20(who%20helmed%20the%20first%20two%20episodes)%20doesn't%20shy%20away%20from%20depicting%20the%20stark%20violence%20and%20betrayal%20of%20her%20youth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20modern-day%20storyline%20is%20less%20compelling%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20so%20far%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jin%20cheng%20and%20jack%20rooney%20in%20three%20body%20problem%2C%20dressed%20in%20historical%20garments%2C%20soaking%20set%2C%20and%20peering%20out%20of%20a%20tub%20of%20water%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eb6e6dce7f1785b2e81784%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJin%20Cheng%20(Jess%20Hong)%20and%20Jack%20Rooney%20(John%20Bradley)%20in%20%26quot%3B3%20Body%20Problem.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EEd%20Miller%2FNetflix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20present%2C%20%26quot%3B3%20Body%20Problem%26quot%3B%20remixes%20some%20Chinese%20characters%20from%20Liu's%20novel%20to%20form%20a%20global%20ensemble%20cast%2C%20with%20most%20of%20the%20action%20taking%20place%20in%20London%20as%20a%20group%20of%20five%20Oxford%20physics%20alums%20get%20caught%20up%20in%20a%20mystery%20that's%20killing%20scientists%20around%20the%20world.%20Meanwhile%2C%20gruff%20intelligence%20officer%20Da%20Shi%20(Benedict%20Wong)%20and%20his%20boss%20Thomas%20Wade%20(%26quot%3BThrones%26quot%3B%20alum%20Liam%20Cunningham%2C%20aka%20Ser%20Davos%20Seaworth)%20attempt%20to%20follow%20the%20trail%20of%20dead%20physicists%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20the%20hell%20is%20going%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B3%20Body%20Problem%26quot%3B%20isn't%20able%20to%20do%20for%20this%20cast%20of%20characters%20what%20it%20does%20for%20Ye%20Wenjie%20in%20those%20rich%2C%20early%20sequences%2C%20and%20at%20times%2C%20its%20myriad%20storylines%20lead%20to%20uneven%20pacing.%20Instead%2C%20the%20show%20works%20best%20when%20it%20allows%20those%20characters%20to%20dive%20into%20the%20meat%20of%20the%20problems%20themselves.%20Some%20of%20the%20show's%20biggest-scale%20%E2%80%94%20and%20most%20intellectually%20intriguing%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0sequences%20take%20place%20in%20a%20virtual%20world%20that%20allows%20Benioff%2C%20Weiss%2C%20and%20Woo%20to%20render%20everything%20from%20a%20planet%20engulfed%20in%20flame%20to%20massive%20armies%20functioning%20as%20computers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20looking%20for%20%26quot%3BThrones%26quot%3B-level%20gore%2C%20in%20or%20out%20of%20this%20virtual%20world%2C%20you'll%20find%20traces%20of%20it%20here%20and%20there.%20Those%20moments%20are%20best%20left%20unspoiled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222043%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22sophon%20in%20three%20body%20problem%2C%20a%20woman%20in%20a%20black%20dress%20with%20a%20sword%20strapped%20to%20her%20back%2C%20walking%20through%20a%20sea%20of%20lava%20and%20flame.%20she%20looks%20threatening%20and%20powerful%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eb6d076080194819fe438a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221532%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20planet%20engulfed%20in%20flame%20in%20%26quot%3B3%20Body%20Problem.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ENetflix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20of%20course%2C%20there%20are%20the%20aliens%2C%20who%2C%20rest%20assured%2C%20are%20definitely%20coming%20to%20Earth.%20%26quot%3B3%20Body%20Problem%26quot%3B%20has%20a%20%26quot%3BContact%26quot%3B-like%20bent%2C%20in%20that%20it%20attempts%20to%20use%20science%20and%20extraterrestrial%20life%20to%20interrogate%20the%20idea%20of%20God%20itself.%20It's%20a%20great%20conceit%2C%20but%20not%20one%20that%20always%20connects%20in%20the%20show%2C%20which%20tends%20to%20deploy%20heavy-handed%20metaphors%20for%20the%20relationship%20between%20humanity%20and%20its%20potential%20conquerors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20discovering%20aliens%20is%20more%20interesting%20than%20going%20to%20war%20with%20them%2C%20at