-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cardi%20B%20tried%20Balut%20eggs%20for%20the%20first%20time%20on%20TikTok%2C%20and%20her%20reaction%20is%20being%20compared%20to%20other%20food%20reviewers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hgetahun%40insider.com%20(Hannah%20Getahun)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-cardi-b-filipino-balut-egg-review-respectful-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Is%20%26quot%3BChroming%26quot%3B%2C%20Latest%20Social%20Media%20Trend%20That%20Killed%2011-Year-Old%20Boy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAn%2011-year-old%20UK%20boy%2C%20Tommie-Lee%20Gracie%20Billington%2C%20died%20attempting%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuk-boy-dies-after-participating-in-dangerous-social-media-challenge-5198038%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710046514869000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3K4Zoo8cuSWhke_cCxp3IZ%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuk-boy-dies-after-participating-in-dangerous-social-media-challenge-5198038%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bchroming%26quot%3B%20challenge%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eat%20a%20friend's%20house.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20boy's%20grandmother%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CHe%20died%20instantly%20after%20a%20sleepover%20at%20a%20friend's%20house.%20The%20boys%20had%20tried%20the%20TikTok%20craze%20of%20'chroming.'%20Tommie-Lee%20went%20into%20cardiac%20arrest%20immediately%20and%20died%20right%20there%20and%20then.%20The%20hospital%20did%20everything%20to%20try%20and%20bring%20him%20back%2C%20but%20nothing%20worked.%20He%20was%20gone.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20%E2%80%98Chroming'%20-%20the%20latest%20trend%20on%20TikTok%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EChroming%2C%20a%20risky%20recreational%20activity%2C%20involves%20inhaling%20hazardous%20household%20chemicals%20and%20substances%20such%20as%20nail%20polish%20remover%2C%20hairspray%2C%20aerosol%20deodorant%2C%20lighter%20fluid%2C%20gasoline%2C%20paint%20thinners%2C%20spray%20paint%2C%20and%20permanent%20markers%2C%20as%20outlined%20by%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.rch.org.au%2Fclinicalguide%2Fguideline_index%2FInhalantsVolatile_Substance_Use_-_Chroming%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710046514869000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1iRr1j8Z_cV56mt0wsa_5K%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rch.org.au%2Fclinicalguide%2Fguideline_index%2FInhalantsVolatile_Substance_Use_-_Chroming%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoyal%20Children's%20Hospital%20Melbourne%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThis%20form%20of%20drug%20use%20creates%20a%20brief%20euphoric%20effect%2C%20but%20according%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40americanaddictioncenters%2Fvideo%2F7268304919654911275%3F_r%253D1%2526_t%253D8kVlu9kNBUs%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710046514869000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1BsEj3bnj5r5NjzkuccTvE%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40americanaddictioncenters%2Fvideo%2F7268304919654911275%3F_r%3D1%26_t%3D8kVlu9kNBUs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Addiction%20Centers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20is%20dangerous%20and%20can%20lead%20to%20adverse%20effects%20like%20dizziness%2C%20vomiting%2C%20cardiac%20failure%2C%20and%20brain%20damage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhen%20inhaled%2C%20these%20chemicals%20are%20absorbed%20into%20the%20bloodstream%20through%20the%20lungs%20and%20can%20affect%20various%20organs.%20The%20cognitive%20abnormalities%20caused%20by%20inhalants%20range%20from%20mild%20impairment%20to%20severe%20dementia.%20Regular%20inhalant%20use%20is%20associated%20with%20high%20rates%20of%20depression%2C%20anxiety%2C%20and%20other%20substance%20abuse%20issues%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Alcohol%20and%20Drug%20Foundation%20based%20in%20Australia.%20While%20inhalants%20may%20not%20directly%20cause%20these%20disorders%2C%20their%20use%20can%20trigger%20or%20exacerbate%20them.%20Additionally%2C%20individuals%20regularly%20using%20inhalants%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20experience%20stressful%20events%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Alcohol%20and%20Drug%20Foundation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ELong-term%20exposure%20to%20these%20toxic%20inhalants%2C%20as%20indicated%20by%20a%202018%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4211428%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710046514869000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3eLSc2Zl-gIwh4gaR2q_j8%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4211428%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20can%20result%20in%20memory%20loss%2C%20lower%20IQ%2C%20an%20inability%20to%20concentrate%2C%20and%20impaired%20judgement.%20Another%20variation%20of%20chroming%20involves%20inhaling%20%26quot%3Bwhippets%26quot%3B%20(also%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Blaughing%20gas%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bhippy%20crack%26quot%3B)%2C%20referring%20to%20cartridges%20filled%20with%20nitrous%20oxide.%20Although%20these%20cartridges%20are%20legally%20used%20to%20inflate%20balloons%2C%20inhaling%20them%20for%20recreational%20purposes%20is%20illegal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20a%202017%20National%20Survey%20on%20Drug%20Use%20and%20Health%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.samhsa.gov%2Fdata%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Freport_3095%2FShortReport-3095.pdf%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710046514869000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw22KHtR9u4cYkK2St2v4Hn3%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samhsa.gov%2Fdata%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Freport_3095%2FShortReport-3095.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20approximately%20684%2C000%20adolescents%20aged%2012%20to%2017%20engaged%20in%20huffing%20or%20inhaling%20toxic%20chemicals%20in%202015.%20The%20report%20also%20highlighted%20a%20total%20of%201.8%20million%20individuals%20aged%2012%20and%20older%20participating%20in%20this%20practice%20that%20same%20year%2C%20with%20inhalant%20use%20typically%20decreasing%20with%20age.%20Around%20one%20in%20five%20kids%20have%20used%20inhalants%20by%20the%20eighth%20grade%2C%20reports%20the%20DEA.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709961420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-06%2F49ef9qsk_social-media-generic-pixabay_625x300_07_June_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-chroming-deadly-tiktok-challenge-claims-life-of-11-year-old-boy-5204726%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%2011-year-old%20boy%20died%20after%20trying%20the%20'chroming'%20trend%2C%20inhaling%20toxic%20chemicals%20that%20experts%20warn%20can%20lead%20to%20serious%20health%20issues%2C%20including%20brain%20damage%20and%20cardiac%20arrest.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-chroming-deadly-tiktok-challenge-claims-life-of-11-year-old-boy-5204726%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-chroming-deadly-tiktok-challenge-claims-life-of-11-year-old-boy-5204726%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-is-chroming-deadly-tiktok-challenge-claims-life-of-11-year-old-boy-5204726%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Anderson's%20Top%205%20performances%3A%20A%20journey%20to%20700%20wickets%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709961365000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108343053%2Cimgsize-62790.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fengland-in-india%2Fjames-andersons-top-five-test-performances-a-journey-to-700-wickets%2Farticleshow%2F108342992.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22England's%20legendary%20fast%20bowler%20James%20Anderson%20became%20the%20first%20paceman%20to%20claim%20700%20Test%20wickets%20during%20the%20fifth%20Test%20against%20India%20on%20Saturday.%20At%2041%2C%20Anderson%20is%20the%20most-capped%20England%20Test%20player%2C%20extending%20his%20record%20to%20187th%20appearance.%20His%20most%20memorable%20Test%20performance%20was%20his%20debut%20against%20Zimbabwe%20in%202003.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dogs%20Licking%20Owners'%20Face%20Is%20Not%20Just%20Unhealthy%2C%20But%20Can%20Even%20Be%20Fatal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAny%20dog%20owners%20reading%20this%20will%20know%20the%20joy%20of%20getting%20home%20and%20being%20greeted%20with%20utter%20delight%20by%20their%20pet%20%E2%80%93%20tail%20wagging%20wildly%20before%20enthusiastic%20but%20face-drenching%20licks.%20While%20some%20owners%20will%20push%20their%20pooches%20away%20playfully%20to%20discourage%20face%20licking%2C%20others%20positively%20revel%20in%20their%20dog's%20affection%20and%20may%20even%20offer%20up%20pursed%20lips%20for%20a%20canine%20kiss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20heartwarming%20scene.%20But%20think%20of%20what%20that%20doggy%20companion%20has%20been%20licking%20throughout%20the%20day.%20Their%20food%20and%20water%2C%20their%20paws%2C%20their%20toys%20and%20chews%20%E2%80%93%20and%20maybe%20their%20bottom%20and%20genitals.%20Do%20those%20cute%20kisses%20seem%20a%20little%20less%20appealing%20now%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20matter%20what%20pets%20have%20licked%2C%20many%20owners%20are%20so%20taken%20with%20their%20dogs%20that%20they're%20willing%20to%20overlook%20the%20potential%20hygiene%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20licking%20is%20important%20for%20dogs.%20It's%20an%20instinctive%20canine%20behaviour.%20When%20dogs%20repeatedly%20lick%20their%20mouths%2C%20it%20can%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0168159196011318%5C%22%3Esubtle%20sign%20of%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20fear%2C%20especially%20when%20combined%20with%20ears%20back%20and%20a%20tense%20expression.%20In%20fact%2C%20observing%20lip%20licking%20frequency%20is%20a%20way%20to%20gauge%20dogs'%20welfare%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS1558787814000070%5C%22%3Etraining%20sessions%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0031938407002582%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%3Ekept%20in%20kennels%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDogs%20also%20use%20lip%20licking%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2Fj.beproc.2017.11.006%5C%22%3Ebehavioural%20response%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20humans'%20emotional%20states.%20Evidence%20suggests%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwoof-dogs-really-can-tell-how-their-owners-are-feeling-new-study-shows-53075%5C%22%3Edogs%20are%20empathetic%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20can%20recognise%20emotions%20in%20both%20humans%20and%20other%20dogs%20using%20visual%20and%20audio%20cues.%20A%20study%20showed%20that%20dogs%20lick%20their%20lips%20more%20frequently%20when%20looking%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2Fj.beproc.2017.11.006%5C%22%3Eangry%20human%20faces%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20dogs%2C%20then%2C%20lip%20licking%20is%20a%20natural%20instinct%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20applies%20to%20relationships%20with%20their%20humans%2C%20too.%20For%20anyone%20living%20with%20a%20dog%2C%20being%20licked%20is%20a%20common%20event%2C%20and%20many%20dogs%20will%20try%20to%20lick%20the%20faces%20and%20mouths%20of%20their%20humans.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F1660-4601%2F17%2F12%2F4300%5C%22%3EAlmost%20half%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20canine%20owners%20report%20being%20licked%20on%20their%20face%20by%20their%20dog.%20But%2C%20given%20the%20penchant%20that%20many%20dogs%20have%20for%20consuming%20items%20owners%20might%20not%20find%20appetising%20(quick%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fexplaining-coprophagy-why-do-dogs-eat-their-own-poo-91273%5C%22%3Epoo%20snack%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20anyone%3F)%20is%20it%20hygienic%2C%20or%20even%20safe%2C%20to%20let%20your%20dog%20lick%20your%20face%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhat%20hides%20within%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOwners%20usually%20love%20their%20dogs%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F13607863.2019.1633620%5C%22%3Edogs'%20companionship%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20affection%20can%20do%20wonders%20for%20their%20owners'%20wellbeing%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Fjournals%2Fpsychology%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Ffpsyg.2022.903647%2Ffull%5C%22%3Emental%20health%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20there's%20no%20doubt%20that%2C%20for%20some%20humans%2C%20canine%20saliva%20might%20do%20more%20harm%20than%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fhealthypets%2Fspecific-groups%2Fhigh-risk%2Forgan-transplant-patients.html%5C%22%3Ewho%20are%20immunocompromised%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20open%20wounds%2C%20or%20a%20dog%20who%20likes%20to%20supplement%20their%20meals%20with%20a%20spot%20of%20coprophagia%20(poop%20eating)%2C%20then%20it's%20best%20to%20avoid%20those%20face%20licks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDogs'%20mouths%20can%20harbour%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmaj.ca%2Fcontent%2F187%2F10%2F736.short%5C%22%3Erange%20of%20microorganisms%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20are%20usually%20low%20risk%20for%20humans.%20However%2C%20in%20rare%20cases%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Ffact-sheets%2Fdetail%2Fzoonoses%5C%22%3Ezoonoses%3C%2Fa%3E%20(infectious%20diseases%20passed%20on%20between%20species)%20can%20be%20transmitted%20from%20dogs%20to%20humans%20by%20bites%2C%20licks%20and%20scratches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FesEOjKNY6xI%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20time%2C%20humans%20who%20come%20into%20contact%20with%20dog%20saliva%20do%20not%20become%20ill.%20In%20fact%2C%20many%20people%20manage%20to%20live%20alongside%20their%20pets%2C%20licks%20and%20all%2C%20without%20encountering%20any%20health%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20are%20rare%20cases%20where%20people%20have%20become%20seriously%20ill%20following%20contact%20with%20dog%20saliva.%20For%20example%2C%20%3Cem%3ECapnocytophaga%20canimorsus%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20bacteria%20found%20in%20the%20mouths%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fhow-deadly-is-your-dogs-saliva-62074%5C%22%3Eup%20to%20three%20quarters%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20otherwise%20healthy%20dogs%20and%20cats%2C%20has%20caused%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasereports.bmj.com%2Fcontent%2F2016%2Fbcr-2016-215450%5C%22%3Elife-threatening%20sepsis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20microbes%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3EPasteurella%20multocida%3C%2Fem%3E%20can%20be%20spread%20by%20contact%20with%20dog%20saliva%2C%20potentially%20resulting%20in%20serious%20outcomes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736(19)30953-5%2Fabstract%5C%22%3Eincluding%20meningitis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20considered%20to%20be%20at%20high%20risk%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1128%2Fcmr.00024-13%5C%22%3Ezoonotic%20infections%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20the%20immunocompromised%2C%20very%20young%20children%2C%20older%20adults%20and%20pregnant%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20fall%20into%20one%20of%20these%20groups%2C%20then%20it's%20in%20your%20interest%20to%20dodge%20dog%20licks.%20Additional%20measures%20should%20also%20be%20implemented%20for%20at%20risk%20dog%20owners.%20Keep%20surfaces%20clean%2C%20minimise%20contamination%20of%20household%20items%20and%20maintain%20scrupulous%20household%20hygiene%20at%20all%20times%2C%20especially%20after%20contact%20with%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAntibiotic%20resistance%20is%20recognised%20as%20a%20major%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unep.org%2Ftopics%2Fchemicals-and-pollution-action%2Fpollution-and-health%2Fantimicrobial-resistance-global-threat%5C%22%3Eglobal%20health%20challenge%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Canine%20saliva%20can%20be%20a%20potential%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F2079-6382%2F11%2F11%2F1490%5C%22%3Esource%20of%20bacteria%3C%2Fa%3E%20carrying%20antibiotic%20resistant%20genes.%20These%20bacteria%20are%20capable%20of%20colonising%20humans%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Fjournals%2Fmicrobiology%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Ffmicb.2020.621597%2Ffull%5C%22%3Eexposure%20to%20dog%20saliva%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.the-microbiologist.com%2Fnews%2Fmulti-drug-resistant-organisms-can-be-transmitted-between-healthy-dogs-and-cats-and-their-hospitalised-owners%2F761.article%5C%22%3Ea%20German%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202%2C800%20hospital%20patients%20and%20their%20companion%20animals%20verified%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20the%20sharing%20of%20multidrug-resistant%20organisms%20between%20companion%20animals%20and%20their%20owners%20is%20possible%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20the%20study%20only%20identified%20a%20handful%20of%20cases.%20The%20researches%20therefore%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fsociety%2F2023%2Fmar%2F19%2Fdogs-and-cats-could-be-passing-on-drug-resistant-bugs-to-owners-study-finds%5C%22%3Econcluded%20that%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9Ccat%20or%20dog%20ownership%20isn't%20an%20important%20risk%20factor%20for%20multidrug-resistant%20organism%20colonisation%20in%20hospital%20patients.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20possible%2C%20then%2C%20that%20being%20licked%20by%20your%20dog%20could%20contribute%20to%20the%20spread%20of%20antibiotic%20resistance%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%20isn't%20likely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FdgQrCELLhso%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EDoctor%20dog%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20potential%20threats%20to%20health%2C%20can%20dog%20licks%20be%20beneficial%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecords%20suggest%20that%20in%20the%20past%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fethnobiomed.biomedcentral.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs13002-017-0175-6%5C%22%3Eanimal%20saliva%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20used%20for%20wound%20healing%2C%20with%20some%20dogs%20specially%20trained%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2F014067369290480Q%5C%22%3Elick%20open%20wounds%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20no%20research%20to%20suggest%20that%20allowing%20animal%20companions%20to%20lick%20wounds%20will%20help%20them%20to%20heal.%20Allowing%20animals%20to%20lick%20open%20wounds%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20could%20put%20an%20owner%20at%20increased%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.liebertpub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1089%2Fvbz.2019.2558%5C%22%3Erisk%20of%20infection%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20relationship%20between%20humans%20and%20their%20dogs%20can%20confer%20other%20potentially%20healing%20benefits.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bacp.co.uk%2Fabout-therapy%2Ftypes-of-therapy%2Fanimal-assisted-therapy%2F%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DAnimal%252Dassisted%2520therapy%2520can%2520help%2Cstruggling%2520with%2520anxiety%2520or%2520depression.%5C%22%3EAnimal-assisted%20therapy%3C%2Fa%3E%20helps%20people%20with%20a%20range%20of%20issues%2C%20such%20as%20anxiety%2C%20eating%20disorders%20and%20trauma.%20Cuddling%20and%20stroking%20dogs%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hopkinsmedicine.org%2Fhealth%2Fwellness-and-prevention%2Fthe-friend-who-keeps-you-young%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DThe%2520cortisol%252Dlowering%2520and%2520oxytocin%2C%25E2%2580%259CIt%2527s%2520relaxing%2520and%2520transcendental.%25E2%2580%259D%5C%22%3Ecan%20help%20patients%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20feel%20calmer%20and%20lower%20blood%20pressure%20and%20heart%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDog%20owners%20tend%20to%20benefit%20from%20their%20pets%20through%20increased%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS1469029216300048%5C%22%3Ephysical%20activity%20and%20social%20connections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20companionship%20and%20improved%20mental%20health.%20Licking%2C%20however%2C%20is%20not%20essential%20to%20the%20close%20bond%20between%20human%20and%20canine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20reason%2C%20for%20most%20people%2C%20letting%20your%20dog%20lick%20you%20is%20probably%20safe.%20With%20good%20management%2C%20healthcare%20(for%20you%20and%20your%20dog)%20and%20excellent%20hygiene%2C%20the%20risks%20of%20an%20occasional%20lick%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20minimal.%20But%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20enforce%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20on%20the%20mouth%E2%80%9D%20rule%2C%20for%20everyone's%20safety.%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F223481%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3Cstrong%3EAuthor%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%