C%22%3Eabruptly%20ousted%20from%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20back%20as%20chief%20executive%20after%20a%20hectic%20saga%20that%20threatened%20to%20sabotage%20OpenAI.%20When%20he%20returned%2C%20Altman%20agreed%20to%20a%20probe%20into%20his%20leadership.%20A%20Thursday%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F03%2F07%2Ftechnology%2Fopenai-executives-role-in-sam-altman-ouster.html%3Fsmid%3Dnytcore-ios-share%26amp%3BreferringSource%3DarticleShare%26amp%3Bsgrp%3Dc-cb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20suggested%20OpenAI%20chief%20technology%20officer%20Mira%20Murati%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-cto-mira-murati-concerns-sam-altman-ouster-nyt-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eraised%20concerns%20about%20Altman's%20leadership%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20board%20members%20prior%20to%20his%20removal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMurati%20disputed%20the%20report%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fmiramurati%2Fstatus%2F1766248214892851241%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshared%20a%20Slack%20message%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20X%20that%20was%20earlier%20sent%20to%20OpenAI%20staff.%20The%20message%20said%20that%20she%20and%20Altman%20%26quot%3Bhave%20a%20strong%20and%20productive%20partnership%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20she%20has%20%26quot%3Bnot%20been%20shy%20about%20sharing%20feedback%20with%20him%20directly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20did%20not%20release%20the%20full%20investigative%20report%2C%20which%20was%20done%20by%20law%20firm%20WilmerHale%2C%20but%20said%20the%20board%20ultimately%20expressed%20full%20confidence%20in%20Altman's%20ongoing%20leadership%20at%20the%20tech%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20418-word%20section%20of%20the%20blog%20post%20offered%20little%20insight%20into%20the%20next%20steps%20for%20OpenAI.%20Still%2C%20the%20company%20did%20say%20it%20was%20adopting%20%26quot%3Bimportant%20imp