w.businessinsider.com%2Fjupiter-moon-europa-ocean-water-plume-evidence-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewater%20is%20one%20key%20ingredient%20for%20life%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20we%20know%20it%2C%20it's%20not%20the%20only%20one.%20There's%20a%20laundry%20list%20of%20other%20chemicals%20that%20scientists%20are%20looking%20for%20%E2%80%94%20oxygen%20being%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Diagram%20of%20Europa's%20inner%20structure.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eb7d55ce7f1785b2e8262a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22665%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20diagram%20shows%20the%20subsurface%20ocean%20lurking%20beneath%20Europa's%20frozen%20crust.%3Cp%3ENASA%20%2F%20JPL-Caltech%20%2F%20Michael%20Carroll%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjuno-jupiter-engine-safe-mode-issues-2016-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA's%20Juno%20spacecraft%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20flying%20around%20Jupiter%20and%20its%20moons%2C%20has%20taken%20the%20most%20precise%20estimate%20of%20Europa's%20oxygen%20production%20to%20date.%20And%20it%20turns%20out%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20less%20than%20we%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20estimate%20of%201%2C000%20tons%20of%20oxygen%20every%2024%20hours%20is%20more%20than%2086%20times%20less%20than%20some%20previous%20estimates.%20And%20this%20new%20data%20may%20call%20Europa's%20habitability%20into%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20Europa%20produces%20oxygen%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOxygen%20production%20looks%20very%20different%20on%20Europa%20than%20on%20Earth.%20Whereas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-amazon-rainforest-is-important-life-support-is-burning-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEarth%20gets%20its%20oxygen%20from%20photosynthesis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Europa's%20is%20a%20result%20of%20its%20parent%20planet%20Jupiter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJupiter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasas-juno-has-completed-its-five-year-journey-to-jupiter-heres-what-the-spacecraft-will-teach-us-about-the-gas-giant-2016-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemits%20powerful%20radiation%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20showers%20Europa%20with%20high-energy%20particles.%20These%20particles%20then%20interact%20with%20frozen%20water%20ice%20(H2O)%20on%20the%20moon's%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221111%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jupiter%20radiation%20belt%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F568c14f6c08a8017028b6ef4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22552%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3Eillustration%20of%20Jupiter's%20powerful%20radiation%20belt%20that%20showers%20nearby%20moons%20with%20high-energy%20particles.%20%3Cp%3EYouTube%2FNASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interaction%20splits%20the%20H2O%20molecules%20apart%20into%20hydrogen%20and%20oxygen%20gas.%20But%20where%20that%20oxygen%20goes%20is%20the%20big%20question.%20Some%20of%20it%20may%20get%20stuck%20in%20the%20ice%2C%20some%20may%20escape%20to%20space%2C%20and%20some%20may%20travel%20downward%20into%20Europa's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearth-water-ice-volume-versus-planets-moons-2016-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubsurface%20ocean%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20enough%20oxygen%20reaches%20underground%2C%20that%20would%20mean%20Europa's%20ocean%20has%20one%20of%20the%20critical%20ingredients%20for%20life%20as%20we%20know%20it.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that's%20a%20big%20question%20mark%20for%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20since%20the%20oxygen%20can%20end%20up%20in%20so%20many%20different%20places%2C%20Niebur%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22europa%20ocean%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F568d7a40c08a809e2f8b4dc0%3Fforma